Question;Answer
What is investiture?;This is the power to choose the bishop.
Did the Pope or the King have the power of investiture?;The Pope and the King fought over this power. Sometimes, the Pope held this power. Sometimes, the King held this power.
What are powers the Pope held over the King?;a) Excommunication: the Pope could kick someone out of the Church, and that meant they were going to hell. b) Interdiction: The Pope could rule that no church services would occur, like no baptisms, no weddings, no funerals. The people would then rise up and force the king to change his policies.
What powers did the king have over the Pope?;The army Feudalism- the king controlled the economy
